<task id="025" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6">
  <metadata>
    <title>D-A-17 Refactor `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` to Invoke `PlaybookExecutionEngine.ExecuteAsync` (Pillar 4)</title>
    <phase>Phase A — Data-driven Foundation</phase>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-effort>5 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>024</dependencies>
    <blocks>028</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, ai, refactoring, chat</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Refactors chat /summarize core orchestrator; removes alternate-key bypass; preserves NFR-13 safety pipeline + streaming JSON delta + session-files filter; tag `bff-api`+`ai`+`refactoring`+`chat`.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Independent orchestrator file; gates 028 integration test.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Refactor `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` to invoke
    `PlaybookExecutionEngine.ExecuteAsync(playbookId: "summarize-document-for-chat@v1", ...)`
    instead of loading the action by alternate key. With the FK chain fixed (task 024),
    the engine traverses playbook → node → action cleanly without the
    `sprk_actioncode` alternate-key lookup.

    Critical-path context: this task closes Pillar 4 — chat `/summarize` finally routes
    through the same `PlaybookExecutionEngine` as the rest of the platform. Project CLAUDE.md
    binding: "MUST route chat `/summarize` through `PlaybookExecutionEngine` (no
    alternate-key bypass after Pillar 4 lands)" + "MUST NOT load action by alternate key in
    chat `/summarize` path after Pillar 4 lands."

    PRESERVATION MANDATORY:
    1. Existing session-files Azure Search filter — UNCHANGED (the orchestrator's chat path
       filters retrieval by sessionId before passing to the engine).
    2. Structured Outputs mode — UNCHANGED (engine respects action's output schema).
    3. Streaming JSON delta — UNCHANGED (engine's existing streaming path is what
       `SummaryHandler` already uses).
    4. NFR-13 safety pipeline middleware chain — UNCHANGED (PromptShield + Groundedness +
       Citations + Privilege + Cross-matter still wraps the call).
    5. NFR-08 11 production node executors — UNCHANGED.

    Regression test required: existing chat /summarize end-to-end test MUST pass with
    byte-equivalent output. Any change to summary text or streaming-delta shape = FAIL.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior BFF engineer with deep `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` + `PlaybookExecutionEngine`
    + chat-streaming experience. Comfortable with NFR-13 safety pipeline preservation +
    streaming JSON delta contracts.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` invokes `PlaybookExecutionEngine.ExecuteAsync` via
    playbookId; alternate-key lookup removed. Existing session-files filter + Structured
    Outputs mode + streaming JSON delta preserved. Safety pipeline + node executors
    unchanged. Regression test passes with byte-equivalent output. Build green;
    publish-size delta reported.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/plan.md</file>
