  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + Rigor Declaration">
      Output: "🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL — chat /summarize orchestrator refactor + NFR-13/-08 preservation binding".
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">
      Verify 024 ✅. Update `current-task.md`.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read inputs + knowledge. Capture baseline publish size. Capture current /summarize output for regression baseline (byte-equivalent target).
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Inspect Current Orchestrator">
      Identify the alternate-key lookup site + the path before/after it. Map the call flow: orchestrator → alternate-key load → action → execution. Plan replacement: orchestrator → engine.ExecuteAsync(playbookId) → playbook → node → action (via FK now valid).
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Refactor Orchestrator">
      Replace alternate-key lookup with `PlaybookExecutionEngine.ExecuteAsync("summarize-document-for-chat@v1", parameters)`. Preserve: session-files Azure Search filter (passed via parameters); Structured Outputs mode (engine respects action's output schema); streaming JSON delta (engine's existing streaming path).
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Add Regression Test">
      Add unit/integration test asserting: chat /summarize end-to-end with a mock session returns byte-equivalent (or semantically-equivalent) output to pre-refactor baseline. Any change in summary text or streaming-delta shape = test fails.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Verify Safety Pipeline Preservation">
      Add test asserting: NFR-13 middleware chain (PromptShield + Groundedness + Citations + Privilege + Cross-matter) still wraps the call. Test passes when middleware order + invocation preserved.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Verify No Alternate-Key Lookups Remain">
      Grep the chat /summarize code path for any remaining `sprk_actioncode` alternate-key usage. MUST return 0 results. Record evidence.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Build + Verify Publish Size + Acceptance Criteria">
      `dotnet build` → 0 errors. `dotnet publish -c Release` → delta vs baseline. Walk each criterion.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `code-review` + `adr-check`. Verify ADR-010 / ADR-013 / ADR-015 / ADR-018 / ADR-029 + NFR-08 / NFR-13 + FR-26 compliance. Both gates MUST pass.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Document + Complete">
      Update task POML status complete. TASK-INDEX 025 ✅. Reset `current-task.md`. Report. Pillar 4 closeout summary.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">build, test, publish</tool>
    <tool name="git">stage + commit changes</tool>
    <tool name="code-review">Quality gate Step 9.5</tool>
